node.text:
In this live stream we used an amazing brain dissection to discuss the hollow spaces in the brain that create the ventricular system for cerebrospinal fluid flow and production. 
.
.

node.text:
MUSCLES OF FACIAL EXPRESSION are the most superficial skeletal muscles in the human body. They run through and attach to the skin of the face. When these muscles contract, they pull on the skin and create the different facial expressions. Many of these muscles are the targets for injections such as botox in order to help reduce the appearance and formation of wrinkles. 
.

node.text:
XIPHOID PROCESS is the smallest inferior segment of the sternum. The sternum has three segments or parts. The upper/most superior portion is called the manubrium, the middle portion is called the body, and again, the lower portion is the xiphoid process. The sternum is used as a landmark for hand placement during CPR. Improper hand placement could result in fracturing of the xiphoid process, potentially damaging organ or other structures. 
.
.

node.text:
MAIN OR PRIMARY BRONCHI are the first branches from the trachea that distributes the air to the left and right lungs. These, along with the more distal bronchi, can become inflamed with the condition known as bronchitis. The right main bronchus is more vertically oriented than the left main bronchus, which means that an aspirated object is more likely to end up in the right main bronchus than the left. 
.
.

node.text:
PERIOSTEUM is a dense irregular connective tissue to surrounds and attaches to the outside of bone tissue. This tissue helps to protect and nourish the bone, and is even involved in fracture repair as the inside layer of this tissue contains bone cells that help with repair. It also acts as an attachment site for tendons and ligaments. 
.
.

node.text:
CALCANEUS or the heel bone is the largest and the strongest of the 7 tarsal (ankle) bones. This bone transmits about 50% of the body’s weight during walking while the other tarsal bones share the rest of the load. This bone also is the attachment site for the calcanea tendon, most often referred to as the Achilles tendon. 
.
.

node.text:
ILEOCECAL VALVE/SPHINCTER is located between the last part of the small intestine called the ileum and the beginning of the large intestine called the cecum (hence the name ileocecal). This valve/sphincter regulates the passage of chyme (mixture of partially digested food and digestive secretions) from the small intestine into the large intestine. 
.
.

node.text:
DEGENERATIVE SPINE can occur from degeneration of the intervertebral discs, degeneration of the vertebral bones (often due to osteoporosis), or a combination of the both. When this occurs in the thoracic spine it results in kyphosis (hunch back), which is an exaggeration of the natural kyphotic curve. 
.
.

node.text:
UTERUS is located between the bladder and the rectum. It is the site of implantation the blastocyst and development of the fetus. The uterus is made up of thee layers: the endometrium, myometrium, and the perimetrium. The endometrium is the inside layer and is highly vascular, and this is the layer that sloughs off during menstruation. The myometrium is composed of smooth muscle, and contraction of this layer occurs during labor and even during menstrual cramping. The perimetrium is the outer layer of the uterus and is composed of epithelial tissue and areolar connective tissue. 
.
.
